{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/using-folium-to-generate-choropleth-map-with-customised-tooltips-12e4cec42af2", "time": 1683006947.034024, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/using-folium-to-generate-choropleth-map-with-customised-tooltips-12e4cec42af2/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "Using Folium to Generate Choropleth Map with Customised Tooltips (Python) | by Carrie Lo | Towards Data Science | Towards Data Science", "h1": "Using Folium to Generate Choropleth Map with Customised Tooltips (Python)", "description": "Folium is a very good package in visualising data on interactive maps. In this demonstration, Hong Kong voter statistics and population data are used. Data were pre-processed and stored in\u2026"}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [{"url": "https://www.voterregistration.gov.hk/chi/statistic2019.html", "anchor_text": "voter statistics", "paragraph_index": 0}, {"url": "https://www.censtatd.gov.hk/hkstat/sub/sp150.jsp?productCode=B1130301", "anchor_text": "population data", "paragraph_index": 0}, {"url": "https://github.com/cydalytics/HK_Voters_Distribution/blob/master/Consolidated%20Data.xlsx", "anchor_text": "Consolidated Data.xlsx", "paragraph_index": 0}, {"url": "https://github.com/cydalytics/HK_Voters_Distribution", "anchor_text": "my Github repo", "paragraph_index": 1}, {"url": "https://abhijeet.carto.com/tables/hkg_adm1/public", "anchor_text": "this site", "paragraph_index": 4}, {"url": "https://github.com/python-visualization/folium", "anchor_text": "official Github repository", "paragraph_index": 15}, {"url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/carrielsc/", "anchor_text": "my linkedIn page", "paragraph_index": 16}, {"url": "https://blog.cyda.hk/", "anchor_text": "https://blog.cyda.hk/", "paragraph_index": 18}], "all_paragraphs": ["Folium is a very good package in visualising data on interactive maps. In this demonstration, Hong Kong voter statistics and population data are used. Data were pre-processed and stored in Consolidated Data.xlsx. Feel free to play around with the dataset =)", "You can directly clone the files from my Github repo.", "folium builds on the data wrangling strengths of the Python ecosystem and the mapping strengths of the leaflet.js library. Manipulate your data in Python, then visualize it in on a Leaflet map via folium.", "Task 1: Generate a Simple Map with Different Tiles", "To plot data on a map, a map json file is needed to locate the position. The json file used in this demonstration is downloaded from this site.", "This defines the initial setting of the base map.", "Folium supports displaying different tiles in the same map, some common map tiles are shown below. You can find the tile type in the caption of each picture.", "This code adds the layer selection button (shown on the top right hand corner) to the map, if this code is missed, the map will be shown with the last added tile and the tile style cannot be changed.", "folium.Choropleth adds the colored layer to the map based on the data, \u2018Proportion\u2019. \u2018Eng_name\u2019 is the key of the data to map with the location of the geojson file. Please ensure the spelling of the location name in the json file is the same as the key in the data.", "Task 2: Prepare Customised Data Label and Display on Map when Hovering", "To add customised data label to a map, folium.features.GeoJsonTooltip is used. By using this code, the labelled values are appended to geojson file.", "First, you need to study the structure of the json file and add the tooltip data to the \u2018properties\u2019. The above script also allows you to find out the map key to be used in the \u2018key_on\u2019 of folium.Choropleth.", "In the tooltip, I want to show the district name in Chinese and the data value. After running the code, you will see the tooltip data appended.", "The plotting script is similar to the one shown in task 1. In the folium.features.GeoJsonTooltip, please choose the variable name that you store the tooltip data. In my example, it is \u2018tooltip1\u2019. labels = False hides the variable name (i.e. \u2018tooltip1\u2019) from showing together with data label.", "There are also some alternatives to add data label to the plot, but I find this approach more convenient. Feel free to comment if you know other ways to add labels. Hope you enjoy my article =)", "To know more about using Folium, please go to official Github repository.", "If you find my article useful, please endorse my skills on my linkedIn page to encourage me to write more articles.", "Your home for data science. A Medium publication sharing concepts, ideas and codes.", "Hong Kong | Data Scientist | Hackathon Enthusiast | Entrepreneur | Public Speaker | https://blog.cyda.hk/"], "all_outgoing_urls": [{"url": "https://rsci.app.link/?%24canonical_url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fp%2F12e4cec42af2&%7Efeature=LoOpenInAppButton&%7Echannel=ShowPostUnderCollection&source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": "Open in app"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fusing-folium-to-generate-choropleth-map-with-customised-tooltips-12e4cec42af2&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign up"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=login&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fusing-folium-to-generate-choropleth-map-with-customised-tooltips-12e4cec42af2&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign In"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/?source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": ""}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fnew-story&source=---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------new_post_sidenav-----------", "anchor_text": "Write"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/search?source=---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------